HEADWORD: Satirist
<hw>Sat"ir*ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>satiriste</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who satirizes; especially, one who
writes satire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mighty <qex>satirist</qex>, who . . . had spread terror
through the Whig ranks.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Satirize</ent>⟦br⟧
